title: England Beats U.S., Giving Each a Glimpse of What’s to Come
description: The U.S. and England can be expected to enter next year’s Women’s World Cup as favorite and challenger. Friday’s game was a chance to establish which team would occupy which role.
dc:creator: Rory Smith
category: United States Women's National Soccer Team
media:description: Lauren Hemp staked England to an early lead at Wembley.
